<DOC><DOCNO> AP880503-0270 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-88 1952EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-MooreMcCormackSale     05-03 0178</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Moore McCormack Sale,0184</SECOND><HEAD>Southdown, Moore McCormack to Sell Energy Unit</HEAD><DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Southdown Inc. and Moore McCormack Resources Inc.announced Tuesday that they will sell a Moore McCormack energysubsidiary for about $148.7 million to CanadianOxy OffshoreProduction Co.   The two resource companies said the proceeds from the sale ofMoore McCormack Energy Inc. will be used to help pay off loans madeto Southdown for its recent $512 million acquisition of MooreMcCormack Resources.   CanadianOxy Offshore Production is a subsidiary of OccidentalPetroleum Corp., a major oil company based in Los Angeles.   The sale of Dallas-based Moore McCormack Energy, which issubject to regulatory approval, is expected to be completed by theend of May following the impending merger of Southdown subsidiarySDW Inc. with Moore McCormack Resources.   Houston-based Southdown and Moore McCormack Resources, based inStamford, Conn., are both engaged in the production of cement andconcrete and in oil and gas operations. Moore McCormack Energyexplores for and produces oil and gas mainly in the Gulf Coast areaof Louisiana and Texas.</TEXT></DOC>